== Cauliflower Rice ==

Heat a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @Riced Cauliflower{250%grams} and cook until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season well with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove from the heat and cover to keep warm until serving.

== Chicken ==

While the cauli rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #large ovenproof frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{240%grams} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned all over, ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

== Prep ==

While the chicken cooks, trim and discard the root and the dark green leafy part from the @Leek{1%unit}. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1%unit} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams} and @Breadcrumbs{25%grams} into a #small bowl{} and add the @Olive Oil{1.5%tbsp} for the crumb. Stir well, then set aside your cheesy breadcrumbs.

== Cooking ==

Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the chicken is browned, add the leek and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%grams} to the pan. Add a drizzle more oil if the pan is dry.

Cook until the mushrooms have browned and the leek has softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Once the veg is soft and the chicken is cooked through, stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams} and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Bring to a boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, pop the contents into an #ovenproof dish{} now.

Sprinkle over the cheesy breadcrumbs, then grill until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Share the cauli rice between your #bowls{}.

Serve the chicken and mushroom crumble on top. Enjoy!